The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and specifically focuses on revenue-maximizing mechanisms (cs.EC). The use of Bayesian single-parameter environments and private values suggests a focus on decision theory and probability (cs.DS), while the investigation of revenue-to-welfare ratios involves optimization and efficiency (cs.AI) as well as statistical analysis (cs.LG).
